  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The efficacy of oral corticosteroids for the treatment of relapses of multiple sclerosis has
      not been proved. French neurologists treat such patients with intravenous corticosteroids.
      The aim of the study is to check if the efficacy of high dose oral methylprednisolone is
      similar to the efficacy intravenous (IV) prednisolone. The main criteria of efficacy is
      symptom recovery within 28 days after inclusion.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
